{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7e993f23-47ac-4146-a96f-8b84ed9bd6b8","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results rather than removing it entirely, so you'll still see it reported.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eb5bc58e-6875-4d57-ae76-10184b01b119","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip/ignore tests with a reason message in four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question that doesn't require any tool calls.","outputTokens":220,"requestId":"BC3B:3595D9:2782D7:2DAC13:69FA939A"},"id":"f40d46e3-2878-4a07-a182-5e6c98fa7b7f","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:04:31.381Z","parentId":"a64890cd-c825-45f5-a03b-243d22b5d43f"}
